The paper discusses deep learning and neural networks architectures for image recognition problems, which are typically categorized under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also explores various activation functions and stopping metrics, which are relevant to neural networks optimization and training, and thus could be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-categories.
